<div style="overflow: auto;">
<h3 style="margin-top: 14px;">Phishing</h3>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<p class="col-9 " style="color:dimgray">This type of attack involves hackers sending malicious email attachments or URLs to users to gain access to their accounts or computer. Cybercriminals are becoming more established and many of these emails are not flagged as spam. Users are tricked into emails claiming they need to change their password or update their billing information, giving criminals access.</p>
